<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c81f50b-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3406"><num value="3406">§ 3406.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration to carry out this subchapter $60,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2023 through 2028 <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002144">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002144"><num>1</num> So in original. Probably should be followed by a period.</note></p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6c81f50c-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/11/tXII/s12006">Pub. L. 111–11, title XII, § 12006</ref>, <date date="2009-03-30">Mar. 30, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/1419">123 Stat. 1419</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/117/263/dJ/tCIII/s10305/g">Pub. L. 117–263, div. J, title CIII, § 10305(g)</ref>, <date date="2022-12-23">Dec. 23, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/3974">136 Stat. 3974</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6c81f50d-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6c81f50e-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id6c81f50f-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2022—<ref href="/us/pl/117/263">Pub. L. 117–263</ref> substituted “this subchapter $60,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2023 through 2028” for “this subchapter—” and struck out pars. (1) to (7) which authorized appropriations for fiscal years 2009 through 2015.</p>
</note>
</notes>
